[5] Cholera - Myanmar (Shan): reported
Date: Tue 5 Apr 2011
Source: XinHuaNet [edited]
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english2010/health/2011-04/05/c_13814058.htm


Cholera has broken out in quake-hit areas in Shan state, Myanmar's
north east, affecting 96 people, according to a local weekly on Tue 5
Apr 2011. Of them, 48 people were in serious condition due to
consumption of unclean drinking water and unhygienic toilet systems in
the region, the Messenger News said.

Due to a recent deadly earthquake that hit Myanmar's north east,
water supply pipes were destroyed, and water in the lake was
contaminated with waste emitting bad smells. Myanmar authorities are
carrying out relief work in the quake-hit areas, while the United
Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF) is providing water purifying tablets
and toilet pipes.

A 7.0-magnitude earthquake jolted Loimwe, 56 km south east of
Kengtung in north eastern Myanmar on the evening of 24 Mar 2011,
killing 73 people and injuring 125 others, according to official
estimation.

